        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[World of Tanks: HEAT closed beta test set for April 16 to 20]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2026/04/world-of-tanks-heat-closed-beta-test-set-for-april-16-to-20</link>
            <guid>1486339</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><p><a title="Companies > Wargaming [4 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/wargaming">Wargaming</a> will host a closed beta test for <a title="Genres > Free-to-Play [512 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/free-to-play">free-to-play</a> tactical vehicle <a title="Genres > Shooter [4,404 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/shooter">shooter</a> <em><a title="Games > World of Tanks: HEAT [1 article]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/world-of-tanks-heat">World of Tanks: HEAT</a></em> from April 16 to 20 across <a title="Platforms > PS5 [11,514 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox Series [8,796 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a>, <a title="Platforms > PC [25,613 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a> (<a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2100280/World_of_Tanks_HEAT/" target="_blank">Steam</a>, Wargaming Game Center), and Nvidia GeForce NOW, the developer announced. Registration is available now via the <a href="https://beta.wotheat.com/" target="_blank">official website</a>. <span id="more-1039451"></span></p><p>Here are the details:</p><blockquote><p>Set in an alternate post World War II era, <em>World of Tanks: HEAT</em> reimagines armored combat, bringing the franchise’s signature gameplay to more dynamic and fast-paced battlefields. Players step into the role of elite Agents with unique, game-changing abilities and pilot a roster of experimental vehicles. Each tank brings its own tactical strengths, enhanced by deep customization with advanced weapon systems, armor modules, and visual upgrades.</p><p>During the closed beta, players will be able to explore a diverse lineup of tanks and Agents, supporting different playstyles across three distinct roles: Defender, Assault, and Marksman. The beta will feature four player-versus-player modes across eight maps:</p><ul><li><strong>Hardpoint</strong> (five-versus-five) – Capture, defend, and hold a rolling series of dynamically changing bases.</li><li><strong>Control</strong> (five-versus-five) – Capture and hold a single zone.</li><li><strong>Kill Confirmed</strong> (five-versus-five) – Destroy enemies and grab their tokens, or grab your allies’ dropped tokens to deny the other team points.</li><li><strong>Conquest</strong> (10-versus-10) – Large teams and multiple capture zones make for a sprawling, dynamic war zone.</li></ul></blockquote><!-- AD: content -->
        <p>Watch a new trailer below. View the screenshots <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/gallery/world-of-tanks-heat/april-9-2026/">at the gallery</a></p><h2><span>Closed Beta Test Trailer</span></h2><p><iframe title="HEAT Closed Beta Starts April 16. Enlist Now!" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ip0AVGHTZ2g?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p><h2><span>Screenshots</span></h2><div id="carousel_1039452"><ul><li><span>❮</span></li><li><span>❯</span></li></ul></div></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2026/04/world-of-tanks-heat-closed-beta-test-set-for-april-16-to-20]]></content:encoded>
            <dc:creator>invalid@example.com (ResetEra_Newsbot</dc:creator>
        </item>
